# OverLanguage: JORKI file gateway workflow
# Local file → compact index → query gateway → LLM selective retrieval

workflow: JorkiFileGateway
intent: let LLMs query huge files by URL/index without full upload

step 1: right-click file in Finder → file_selected
step 2: local C++ engine creates compact searchable index → local_index
step 3: compute SHA256 and Merkle root → file_identity
step 4: upload index to Hugging Face Space → query_gateway
step 5: LLM reads /meta endpoint → file_metadata
step 6: LLM reads /summary endpoint → file_summary
step 7: LLM searches /search for candidate locations → search_results
step 8: LLM retrieves /chunk for necessary ranges → file_chunks
step 9: LLM queries /query/sql for read-only SELECT → sql_results
step 10: verify merkle_root and receipt fields → integrity_verified
step 11: revoke URL when session ends → url_revoked
step 12: confirm post-revoke 404 → access_closed

artifact: query_gateway
artifact: file_identity
receipt: SHA256 chained from file selection to revocation confirmation
value: AI file gateway for large local artifacts — not file transfer, context transfer
